text = "**User Manual: Better Garden Planner**

Thank you for choosing Better Garden Planner! 
This user manual will guide you through the features and functionality of the solution. 
Please refer to the instructions below to make the most of the application.

## Table of Contents

1. Introduction
2. System Requirements
3. Installation
4. User Interface Overview
5. Creating a New Project
6. Managing Your Garden
7. Saving and Loading Projects
8. Printing Your Garden Plan
9. Exporting Your Garden Plan
10. Troubleshooting
11. Feedback and Support

## 1. Introduction

Better Garden Planner is a comprehensive garden planning tool designed to assist 
gardeners in visualizing and organizing their garden layouts. 
The solution provides a user-friendly interface with features such as drag-and-drop 
functionality, object library, and note-taking capabilities. 
With Better Garden Planner, you can create, manage, and save your garden plans 
effortlessly.

## 2. System Requirements

- Operating System: Windows 10, macOS, or Linux
- Processor: Dual-core processor or higher
- RAM: 2GB or higher
- Storage: 200MB of free disk space
- Display: 1024x768 resolution or higher

## 3. Installation

To install Better Garden Planner, follow these steps:

1. Visit the official website [www.bettergardenplanner.com]
(www.bettergardenplanner.com) and navigate to the \"Downloads\" section.
2. Choose the appropriate installer for your operating system.
3. Run the installer and follow the on-screen instructions to complete the installation 
process.
4. Once the installation is complete, launch the application.

## 4. User Interface Overview

Upon launching Better Garden Planner, you will be presented with the main interface, 
which consists of the following components:

![User Interface](screenshots/ui_overview.png)

1. **Menu Bar**: The menu bar contains various options for managing your projects, 
accessing help documentation, and adjusting application settings.
2. **Toolbar**: The toolbar provides quick access to frequently used tools and functions,
such as creating new projects, saving, and printing.
3. **Object Library**: The object library contains a collection of predefined garden 
objects and plants that can be dragged and dropped onto the garden canvas.
4. **Garden Canvas**: The garden canvas is the main area where you can design
and arrange your garden layout. You can drag objects from the object library onto the 
canvas and arrange them as per your requirements.
5. **Notebook**: The notebook allows you to create and manage notes related to your 
garden. You can add, edit, and delete notes to keep track of important information.
6. **Status Bar**: The status bar displays useful information, such as the current 
project name, zoom level, and any notifications or error messages.

## 5. Creating a New Project

To create a new project and start designing your garden, follow these steps:

1. Click on the \"File\" menu in the menu bar and select \"New Project.\"
2. Enter a name for your project and choose a location to save it.
3. Click \"Create\" to create the new project.
4. The garden canvas will be cleared, and you can start designing your garden layout.

## 6. Managing Your Garden

Better Garden Planner offers several features to help you manage your garden 
effectively. Here are some key functions:

- **Adding Objects**: To add an object to your garden, simply click on an object 
from the object library and drag it onto the garden canvas. You can position and 
resize the objects as needed.
- **Arranging Objects**: Objects on the garden canvas can be moved by clicking and 
dragging them to the desired location. You can also resize objects by clicking and 
dragging the resize handles.
- **

Deleting Objects**: To remove an object from the garden canvas, select it and press the 
\"Delete\" key or right-click on the object and choose \"Delete\" from the context menu.
- **Note-Taking**: The notebook feature allows you to create and manage notes 
related to your garden. Click on the notebook tab to access the note-taking interface. 
You can add new notes, edit existing notes, and delete notes as needed.

## 7. Saving and Loading Projects

Better Garden Planner provides options to save and load your garden projects for 
future reference. Follow these steps to save and load your projects:

- **Saving a Project**:
   1. Click on the \"File\" menu in the menu bar and select \"Save Project\" or use the
shortcut Ctrl+S (Windows) or Command+S (macOS).
   2. Choose a location to save your project and enter a name for the project file.
   3. Click \"Save\" to save the project.

- **Loading a Project**:
   1. Click on the \"File\" menu in the menu bar and select \"Load Project.\"
   2. Browse to the location where your project file is saved.
   3. Select the project file and click \"Open\" to load the project.

## 8. Printing Your Garden Plan

Better Garden Planner allows you to print your garden plan for reference or sharing.
 To print your garden plan, follow these steps:

1. Click on the \"File\" menu in the menu bar and select \"Print\" or use the shortcut Ctrl+P 
(Windows) or Command+P (macOS).
2. Adjust the print settings, such as page orientation, margins, and scale, as desired.
3. Click \"Print\" to print your garden plan.

## 9. Exporting Your Garden Plan

In addition to printing, Better Garden Planner enables you to export your garden plan as 
an image file for digital sharing or further editing. To export your garden plan, follow 
these steps:

1. Click on the \"File\" menu in the menu bar and select \"Export\" or use the shortcut Ctrl+E 
(Windows) or Command+E (macOS).
2. Choose a location to save the exported image and enter a file name.
3. Select the desired image format (e.g., PNG, JPEG) from the available options.
4. Click \"Save\" to export your garden plan as an image file.

## 10. Troubleshooting

If you encounter any issues or have questions while using Better Garden Planner, 
please refer to the following resources:

- **Contact Us**: If you need further assistance, you can reach out to our support 
team by emailing support@bettergardenplanner.com.

## 11. Feedback and Support

We value your feedback and are constantly working to improve Better Garden Planner. 
If you have any suggestions, feature requests, or encounter any issues, please let us know. 
You can provide feedback through the following channels:

- Email: feedback@bettergardenplanner.com
- Website: [www.bettergardenplanner.com/feedback]
(www.bettergardenplanner.com/feedback)

Thank you for using Better Garden Planner! Happy gardening!"

